~FT--==--==--==->-==--==--==-<-==--==--==--==--==--==-<-==--==--==->-==--==--==--
~FYCommand Name~CB:~RS bank
~FT--==--==--==->-==--==--==-<-==--==--==--==--==--==-<-==--==--==->-==--==--==--
Command Usage: .bank [<option>] [<arguments>]
  
Synopsis:
  If used alone, and the user is using the RaMTITS menu system, the user
  will then be brought into the bank menu where they will be prompted for
  what they want to do.  You can get a general idea on what the different
  choices do by reading below what the different command line options are.
  If you aren't using the menu system, then you will be given a list of
  options to use:

  ~CW'~CRdmoney  ~CW'~CB: ~CRUsage~CB:~CR .bank dmoney ~CB[~CRamount to deposit~CB]
                This option lets the user deposit however much they want
                into the bank. If they want to deposit all their money, just
                enter '1' for the amount.

  ~CW'~CRwmoney  ~CW'~CB: ~CRUsage~CB:~CR .bank wmoney ~CB[~CRamount to withdrawal~CB]
                This option lets the user withdrawal however much they want
                from the bank. If they want to withdrawal all their money,
                just enter '1' for the amount.

  ~CW'~CRdchips  ~CW'~CB: ~CRUsage~CB:~CR .bank dchips ~CB[~CRamount to deposit~CB]
                This option lets the user deposit however much they want
                into the bank. If they want to deposit all their chips, just
                enter '1' for the amount.

  ~CW'~CRwchips  ~CW'~CB: ~CRUsage~CB:~CR .bank wchips ~CB[~CRamount to withdrawal~CB]
                This option lets the user withdrawal however much they want
                from the bank. If they want to withdrawal all their chips,
                just enter '1' for the amount.

  ~CW'~CRtransfer~CW'~CB:~CR Usage~CB:~CR .bank transfer ~CB[~CRuser~CB] [~CRmoney~CW|~CRchips~CB] [~CRamount~CB]
                This option lets the user transfer however much money or
                chips into the user of their choice bank account. In order
                for this to work, the specified user must be online, and
                they must have the amount of money or chips that they
                specified.

~FT--==--==--==->-==--==--==-<-==--==--==--==--==--==-<-==--==--==->-==--==--==--

